{
  "text": "OVA exposure remains the common method to mimic asthma in mice [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In this study, the OVA-exposed mice displayed remarkably enhanced bronchial reactivity to methacholine, compared to the control group. Moreover, pathological lung tissue images indicate that inflammatory cells have notably infiltrated into the connective tissues around the bronchiole and blood vessels in the model group. The inflammation score between normal mice and OVAexposed mice demonstrated a statistically significant difference. These findings verify successful construction of the allergic asthma mouse model.",
